Held - A Short Film by Jake Nova. üé•
Sometimes what we hold onto, holds us back. ü•Ä

üé¨ Excited to share my project; a short film Held by myself. The story explores enotional containment and masking emotions ‚Äî a theme that resonated with me and one I believe needs to be shared more.

This was a self-tape project I created as part of building my portfolio, and I‚Äôm proud of the professional approach and care that went into it. Although recorded in a few takes and slightly rushed due to environment I‚Äôm currently living in, I am always practicing and expanding my skills to excel in this career.

I‚Äôm Always looking to grow and connect with representation and collaborators who are looking for talent üé≠

message.text:
Save the date: 30 March 2026.

Actors don‚Äôt need another generic ‚Äúask ChatGPT‚Äù shortcut. We need clarity under pressure. No time left, the self-tape‚Äôs due and you‚Äôre still second-guessing every beat?

The Actors Copilot is human-led, AI-assisted: AI helps you organise, highlight and break things down‚Ä¶ so you can focus on the work that actually matters.

And it goes far beyond tools. Inside the platform we will have interactive zoom sessions that go  deeply into what it is to be an actor: craft, mindset, industry realities, and the inner work‚Äîhow to mine your past, sharpen your instincts, and make braver, truer choices on tape and on set.

30 March 2026. Follow for the build-up.

#TheActorsCopilot #Actors #ActorLife #WorkingActor #SelfTape SelfTapeAuditions CharacterWork ActingCoach ActingTraining AuditionPrep AIForActors FilmTV Casting ActorCommunity

items.text:
My short thriller Existential Cow Film is 80% cast, 2 people left to find.

Evelyn Baxter, the star of an in-universe book, makes an appearance. Her moment is one of the more surreal parts of the story. Age: 20-30

Maxine Paloma, a charismatic and friendly Jimmy Fallon esque talk-show host, a very human and empathetic personality (with an edge, of course) Any age welcome. 

The deadline for auditions is this Sunday for Maxine Paloma- don't miss out on being a part of an experimental, disturbing dark comedy! 

Email ognimasoriginals@gmail.com for audition materials.

I‚Äôm an Executive Producer building a **small, reliable team** to create content consistently with the goal of turning that work into **paid opportunities** with businesses and brands.

To be clear: my title doesn‚Äôt mean I‚Äôm throwing money at people. I‚Äôm looking for creatives who are willing to **invest in themselves**, show up, and build leverage through real work. This is a **team effort** ‚Äî the work we create together is what opens doors.

If pitching or outreach isn‚Äôt your strength yet, we can align through a workshop. The goal is shared success, not gatekeeping.

If you‚Äôre ready to level up, I‚Äôll make sure you‚Äôre positioned for more opportunities and growth ‚Äî **but we move as a team**.

If this resonates, comment or DM. If not, clarity saves us both time.

CASTING CALL - BRIGHTON üé¨ 16+ MALE ACTOR WANTED
We‚Äôre casting for BITE, a MET Film graduate short film, and we‚Äôre looking for a local 16+ actor to join our cast!

ABOUT THE FILM

When Kev Mullen gets sacked from his job, 14-year-old Billy and loyal staffy, Ruby, are forced to bear the brunt of his father‚Äôs downfall. Led by Billy‚Äôs narration, BITE follows the attempt to navigate his father‚Äôs increasing alcoholism, volatility, and ostracisation. The screenplay has already been praised by screenwriter Rob Williams and we are hoping for big things with this film.

THE ROLE - ‚ÄòOLDER BOY‚Äô

A rough schoolmate who gives Billy and his dog a hard time. 

‚Ä¢ Paid according to equity guidelines

WE‚ÄôRE LOOKING FOR:

‚Ä¢ Male actor, 16+

‚Ä¢ Brighton-based

‚Ä¢ One day of filming during the week of the 16th February

To apply, please email 1195873@sfsstudents.ac.uk with your headshots/picture. No previous experience required. Thank you! üé•

Led by Billy‚Äôs narration, BITE follows the attempt to navigate his father‚Äôs increasing alcoholism, volatility, and ostracisation. The screenplay has already been praised by screenwriter Rob Williams and we are hoping for big things with this film.

THE ROLE - ‚ÄòOLDER BOY‚Äô

A rough schoolmate who gives Billy and his dog a hard time. 

‚Ä¢ Paid according to equity guidelines

WE‚ÄôRE LOOKING FOR:

‚Ä¢ Male actor, 16+

‚Ä¢ Brighton-based

‚Ä¢ One day of filming during the week of the 16th February

To apply, please email 1195873@sfsstudents.ac.uk with your headshots/picture. No previous experience required. Thank you! üé•

Produktionen brauchen nicht immer gro√üe Worte, sondern Menschen, die ein Bild tragen. Pr√§senz, Haltung und Glaubw√ºrdigkeit entscheiden oft dar√ºber, ob eine Szene funktioniert oder nicht. Genau hier positioniere ich mich. Als Speaking Extra, Nebendarsteller und Featured Extra bringe ich Ruhe, Struktur und Authentizit√§t ins Bild, ob in Werbung, Serie, Kino oder Showformaten. 

Ich wirke dort, wo Realit√§t gefragt ist. Institutionelle Rollen, berufliche Kontexte, Alltagsfiguren mit Profil. Kameraerfahren, setdiszipliniert und flexibel einsetzbar, deutschlandweit und zuverl√§ssig. Keine √úberzeichnung, kein Theater, sondern glaubhafte Pr√§senz, die Regie und Casting Sicherheit gibt. 

Du suchst eine sichtbare Nebenrolle oder eine fokussierte Figur mit Wirkung? Dann melde Dich direkt bei mir.

NOW ACCEPTING SUBMISSIONS IN THE GREATER LOS ANGELES AREA

SOUTHERN FRIED FUNERAL by J. Dietz Osborne and Nate Eppler

Non union theatre 

Produced by the JFed Players 
As affiliated with the Jewish Federation of the Greater San Gabriel and Pomona Valleys 

Some details:
Callbacks are in-person on Thursday February 12 in Monrovia. 

Rehearsals start February 22 in Monrovia. They will be Monday, Tuesday, Thursday nights and Sunday days, for the most part. 

Tech week begins April 25 or 26. All cast members must be fully available for tech week.

Performances will be at Ahiah Center for Spiritual Living Pasadena and will be:
Saturday, May 2 evening
Sunday, May 3 matinee 
(Wednesday, May 6 - pickup rehearsal)
Thursday, May 7 evening
Saturday, May 9 evening
Sunday, May 10 (Mother's Day) matinee
Sunday, May 10 (Mother's Day) evening show closing

Please only submit if you're available for all tech week, pickup rehearsal, and all performances.

Selected Actors will be asked to submit self tape auditions. Character breakdowns are below. 

[DOROTHY FRYE] 50s/60s female., Dewey Frye‚Äôs widow and the matriarch of the family. Strong-willed, grieving widow but also snarky and fun. Strong actor with great comedic timing. AUTHENTIC SOUNDING MISSISSIPPI OR SOUTHERN ACCENT. Lead

[SAMMY JO FRYE-LEFETTE] 30s, female. the middle child and future president of the Junior League. Maybe some anger issues, wears the pants in the marriage. Strong actor with great comedic timing. AUTHENTIC SOUNDING MISSISSIPPI OR SOUTHERN ACCENT.

[HARLENE FRYE] 30s/40s, female. the oldest child and prodigal daughter. Strong actor with great comedic timing. AUTHENTIC SOUNDING MISSISSIPPI OR SOUTHERN ACCENT

[DEWEY FRYE JR] 20s, male. the youngest child and not the brightest bulb. Strong actor with great comedic timing. AUTHENTIC SOUNDING MISSISSIPPI OR SOUTHERN ACCENT

[DUB FRYE] 50s/60s, male. Dorothy‚Äôs brother-in-law. Charmingly manipulative. Strong actor with great comedic timing. AUTHENTIC SOUNDING MISSISSIPPI OR SOUTHERN ACCENT

[ATTICUS ‚ÄúATTIE‚Äù VAN LEER] 30s/40s, male, family lawyer and on-again off-again love interest of Harlene. Intellectual. Strong actor with great comedic timing. AUTHENTIC SOUNDING MISSISSIPPI OR SOUTHERN ACCENT

[BEECHAM LEFETTE] 30s, male . Sammy Jo‚Äôs husband. Slightly argumentative, doesn't appreciate being misrepresented. Strong actor with great comedic timing. AUTHENTIC SOUNDING MISSISSIPPI OR SOUTHERN ACCENT

[MARTHA ANN FOX] 50s/60s, female. Dorothy‚Äòs best friend, first name pronounced ‚ÄúMarthann." Rather crass and to the point, like Dorothy from Golden Girls. Strong actor with great comedic timing. AUTHENTIC SOUNDING MISSISSIPPI OR SOUTHERN ACCENT

[FAIRY JUNE COOPER] 50s/60s, female. contemporary of Dorothy and Martha Ann; they‚Äôve been friends since high school. Kind of prude and clueless, well meaning. Strong actor with great comedic timing. AUTHENTIC SOUNDING MISSISSIPPI OR SOUTHERN ACCENT

[BENNY CHARLES GREENWOOD] 50s/60s male, best friend of Dewey Frye Sr. Sincere friend to the family. Not a large role, only a few scenes with some dialogue but present throughout

[OZELLA MEEKS] 60s/70s, female. chairwoman of a community committee, a position she does not take lightly. Her life's goal is organizing and planning while following rules. Strong actor with great comedic timing. AUTHENTIC SOUNDING MISSISSIPPI OR SOUTHERN ACCENT

Storyline: Dewey Frye is dead and the rest of his family is left to pick up the pieces ‚Äì that is if they don't kill each other first. Funerals bring out the worst, the best, and the funniest in people, and the Fryes are no exception. A big-hearted comedy about family ‚Äì Southern-style.

Please submit headshots and resumes and availability to JFedProd@gmail.com 

And feel free to spread the word or share with others you think are a good fit.

Which is a huge driving force for my personality, I‚Äôve learned more about myself and grew close with my crew and developed a team. Thanks to you all that have assisted with this project and we have more to go before we accomplish the mission. For any filmmakers needing crew to start up your project and vision contact me. The dots always connect Last of the Force coming soon as well as more projects in the pipeline. Enjoy these films out now with a quick search on the tube.

items.text:
****CASTING CALL SHORT FILM****

**TITLE: PURPLE INK**

**SYNOPSIS: **The film tells the story of Chase, a teenager with undiagnosed juvenile arthritis, who makes an unlikely friendship with Daren, an old man, during his time at physical therapy.

It is a hopeful story that explores friendship, the acceptance of one's body, and aims to shed light on the disabled youth community, especially those with invisible disabilities that may go undiagnosed or untreated for many years. I grew up with the disease, which greatly limited my mobility and quality of life. Over 300k kids in the US today have some sort of rheumatoid disability, with a large number of them going undiagnosed and untreated. I hope that this film will help destigmatize and bring awareness to what youth disabilities can look like.

**Tentative Filming Dates:** August 26th-30th, 2026

Production Locations: Boston Area

Union + Non-Union. UNPAID. Actors will receive 3 on-set meals and will be compensated for travel and housing.

Project Length: 4 days 

**Please email headshot, reel, and self-tape to [colin_dowse@emerson.edu](mailto:colin_dowse@emerson.edu)

***ROLES:***

**CHASE **Male-Presenting, Any Ethnicity, 16-22 years old

Deeply introspective, Chase has juvenile arthritis and struggles with walking and pain in his lower body. He thinks this holds him back, but in reality, it makes him uncommonly observant and wise for his age. He's smart as a whip and a big classic rock fan, which helps him bond with Daren, his elderly counterpart, who helps him to accept his body for what it is and learn to love himself.

**DAREN **Male-Presenting, Any Ethnicity, 60-80 years old

A soft-spoken retired fishing captain who is admitted to physical therapy due to hip troubles. His health issues place a strain on his relationships. Meeting Chase, who struggles similarly, he develops a paternal bond with him, wishing to share his life's wisdom to help him out of his rut. In helping Chase, he learns a lot about himself.

**Please email headshot, reel, and self-tape to [colin_dowse@emerson.edu](mailto:colin_dowse@emerson.edu)

***ROLES:***

**CHASE **Male-Presenting, Any Ethnicity, 16-22 years old

Deeply introspective, Chase has juvenile arthritis and struggles with walking and pain in his lower body. He thinks this holds him back, but in reality, it makes him uncommonly observant and wise for his age. He's smart as a whip and a big classic rock fan, which helps him bond with Daren, his elderly counterpart, who helps him to accept his body for what it is and learn to love himself.

**DAREN **Male-Presenting, Any Ethnicity, 60-80 years old

A soft-spoken retired fishing captain who is admitted to physical therapy due to hip troubles. His health issues place a strain on his relationships. Meeting Chase, who struggles similarly, he develops a paternal bond with him, wishing to share his life's wisdom to help him out of his rut. In helping Chase, he learns a lot about himself.

Only one space left for our upcoming Demidov Two Day Intensive running May 23rd & 24th at Pushkin House in London! 

This Two Day Intensive will introduce actors to Demidov‚Äôs unique approach to accessing our inner freedom, cultivating our intuition, perception, spontaneity, and ability to surrender fully to our inner urges and the truth of our experience in the moment. 

Over the course of this weekend, we will discover how to orient ourselves in the circumstances of a given text and to surrender to them fully. We will learn how circumstances become 'given', and how they become clearer and deeper every time we repeat a scene. We will learn to let ourselves be driven by the force of circumstances, rather than forcing ourselves to do, think or feel anything. In this way, living as character becomes effortless and spontaneous.

This Intensive is for actors both new to the Demidov work, and also for those who would like to go deeper into it. 

The Demidov Organic Acting Technique empowers actors to connect deeply with their unique creative individuality by guiding them to recognise and trust their innate artistic instincts. It is an approach that cultivates faith in the actors‚Äô own talent and foster spontaneous performances that emerge organically, allowing actors to consistently access inspiration and fully express their true creative potential. 

Click the link below to read more and email us at [office@demidovstudiolondon.com](mailto:office@demidovstudiolondon.com) with any questions!

https://www.demidovstudiolondon.com/courses/demidov-two-day-intensive-may26

~

The UK‚Äôs only certified Demidov Acting School

Located at Pushkin House, 5a Bloomsbury Square, London WC1A 2TA

[demidovstudiolondon.com](http://demidovstudiolondon.com/)

All classes and courses taught by studio Founder & Director @andrei_biziorek 

@pushkinhouselondon

CASTING CALL ‚Äì DRAMATIC SHORT FILM

Project Title: When the Light Fades
Type: Independent Short Film (Drama / Psychological Realism)
Production Dates: February 21st & 22nd 
Location: Denver, CO 
Compensation: $1,000 Total + IMDb Credit + Footage for Reel

SYNOPSIS
When the Light Fades is an intimate portrait of resilience and regret in a town on the brink of collapse.
After a local factory shutdown upends their lives, three young adults must face the truths they‚Äôve spent years avoiding  about love, loyalty, and the silent compromises that shape who we become.
Through quiet moments and raw confrontation, the film explores what it means to hold onto hope when everything around you is falling apart.

ROLES NEEDED

LEAD ROLES
ARIA (Female, 19‚Äì23, Any Ethnicity)
A talented photographer caring for her sick mother. Driven yet conflicted, she‚Äôs torn between duty and the life she dreams of. Vulnerability and quiet strength define her journey.

MARCUS (Male, 20‚Äì24, Any Ethnicity)
A loyal factory worker hiding the truth about the plant‚Äôs closure. His calm exterior masks deep guilt and fear of failure. Must convey emotional restraint and inner turmoil.

NIA (Female, 18‚Äì22, Any Ethnicity)
A passionate former student activist returning home disillusioned. Restless, outspoken, and emotionally volatile. She challenges others  and herself to confront uncomfortable realities.

SUPPORTING ROLES
ZOE (Female, 17‚Äì20, Any Ethnicity)
Marcus‚Äôs younger sister. Sharp and perceptive beyond her age. She sees the fractures the older characters can‚Äôt and forces them to confront uncomfortable truths.

MRS. JACOBS (Female, 60s‚Äì70s, Any Ethnicity)
A retired teacher and quiet pillar of the community. Offers grounded wisdom and emotional perspective amid the chaos.

TO SUBMIT
Please email the following materials to everlastfilming@gmail.com 
Current headshot
Acting r√©sum√© or demo reel (if available)
Role(s) you‚Äôre submitting for
City of residence

CASTING - BLOOD & PAPER

Genre: Drama, Coming of Age

Synopsis: After a violent altercation leaves her suspended from school, anger-prone Demi becomes obsessed with obtaining her Tribal ID to prove that she belongs somewhere. But as her need to protect others pushes them farther away, she must confront the realization that identity is not something you can find on a piece of paper.

Roles:

DEMI: (Late teens/early 20‚Äôs, Female, Black/African Descent, Racially Ambiguous, Lead)

A high schooler with anger issues, a lack of friends, but a fierce loyalty to protect those around her. None of her emotions come with a middle ground: when she‚Äôs sad, she‚Äôs inconsolable, when she‚Äôs angry, she‚Äôs furious. Ends up pushing people away due to this nature. Begins an obsessive attempt to obtain her Tribal ID in hopes that it will make her feel like she belongs somewhere.

LENA: (Late teens/early 20‚Äôs, Female, Any Ethnicity, Supporting)

Demi‚Äôs Older Sister. Loves and cares for Demi, but secretly holds some resentment towards the problem child that is her sister. She is moving across the country for college, and is worried how Demi will do without her there.

ADRIAN: (Late teens/early 20‚Äôs, Male, Native American/Indigenous Descent, Hispanic/Latino, Supporting)

An attractive, native farm hand, and childhood best friend of Demi. He admires her protective nature, and has always had a crush on her .. though Demi has always been too oblivious to notice.

DRUNKARDS: (20-30, Male, Any Ethnicity)

Two drunk men on the street who catcall Lena, not realizing that doing so will incur the wrath of Demi.

FINAL CASTING CALL!
COMIC CON DOCUMENTARY | CASTING CALL 

Hello,

I am currently on my BA Hons Degree in Media Production at South Gloucestershire and Stroud College. 

I am doing a 6 - minute documentary that uses a core participants to explore how Cosplay is not a performance but entertainment, a way identity is expressed, shaped and performed.

It will document the participants' experience and highlight the experience from a first - time attendees, offering both a personal insight and broader perspective of UK Comic Con Culture. 

I need someone to Cosplay Catwoman aged 18 - 40 at Bristol Comic Con on the 8th March 2026 at Ashton Gate Stadium. 

There will also be an interview segment following the event.

Please let me know if you'd be interested?

I will pay for your ticket too, it's from 10:30am - 16:00pm

I'd pay you ¬£200.00

It's for my BA Hons Degree FMP and determines if I pass or fail.

**CASTING CALL: PROFESSOR WILLARD**

**Supporting Role | SCAD Senior Thesis Film // *****Opulence***

**March 5-8th, 2026 | Savannah, GA**

**Logline: **

When a Black woman becomes exhausted by passive-aggressive racism at her college, she finds inspiration and connection through a myth of Black angels sent by God.

**Professor Willard (Late 30‚Äôs-50‚Äôs, White, Male):** 

A public speaking professor at Grove Technical College for five years, originally from a small town in Michigan, now living in the DMV after relocating for his wife, Iyla (African American), who works in D.C. Willard is passionate, articulate, and well-meaning; he teaches with enthusiasm, mentors his students, and doesn‚Äôt tolerate disrespect, yet struggles to speak up publicly when racism and microaggressions arise. He privately supports Myra but hesitates within institutional systems. Outside of work, he enjoys quiet nights with his wife, debating over coffee (one sugar), and taking samba classes on Tuesday nights. The role explores the tension between genuine allyship and passive complicity; not a white savior.

**Contact:**

Producer | Hannah Ballard // hballard9hb@gmail.com

Director | Music Miranda // mmiran21@student.scad.edu

*Please submit a headshot and resum√© via email for more information.  *

*credit & copy of the film comp.

KENT and SUSSEX AREAS
Science Boffins is currently looking for more phenomenal Science Boffins to help us to bring science to life for primary school children. We have parties, schools and events throughout the year.

You don't need a formal background in science as we teach you everything you'll need to know.

All you need is access to a car (unless London based), the ability to work some weekends/weekdays and the desire to launch rockets, concoct potions and generally share just how much fun science can be.

HOW DOES BEING A SCIENCE BOFFIN WORK?

For the right person, this could be the most fun way of making an extra income.

You'll get to enjoy inspiring and educating children, having a fantastic time and getting paid along the way. You'll travel to an event in your local area and bring science to life for primary school age children with some brilliant science experiments.

Are you a fun, enthusiastic and reliable person and able to communicate effectively and promptly to potential bookings? Then join a nationwide team of 40+ well-paid Science Boffin presenters.  We have a strong reputation, rave reviews, and the privilege of working with some globally recognised companies.

We're a friendly bunch and have a (we think!) cracking training program to help you get up to speed. If that sounds like you? You too can become one of our amazing Science Boffins and bring science alive to children.

Looking forward to hearing from you.

Annette

Science Boffins

Your ùóøùó≤ùóΩùó≤ùóÆùòÅùóÆùóØùóπùó≤ ùóΩùòÄùòÜùó∞ùóµùóºùóπùóºùó¥ùòÜ ùòÇùóªùó±ùó≤ùóø ùóΩùóøùó≤ùòÄùòÄùòÇùóøùó≤.

In The Actors Copilot, we call this your ùó£ùó≤ùóøùòÄùóºùóªùóÆùóπ ùóóùó°ùóî and you can ùóΩùóπùòÇùó¥ ùó∂ùòÅ ùó∂ùóªùòÅùóº ùóÆùóªùòÜ ùóøùóºùóπùó≤ ùó≥ùóÆùòÄùòÅ.

üíé Casting type is what you ùóÆùóøùó≤. Archetype is what you ùó±ùóº under pressure.
üíé Casting type can shift with ùó∞ùóºùóªùòÅùó≤ùòÖùòÅ. Archetype always shows up under ùóΩùóøùó≤ùòÄùòÄùòÇùóøùó≤.
üíé Casting type gets you the audition. Archetype gives you the nuance.
üíé If you only play type, you‚Äôre ùó∞ùóºùóøùóøùó≤ùó∞ùòÅ. If you play archetype, you‚Äôre ùó∞ùóºùó∫ùóΩùó≤ùóπùóπùó∂ùóªùó¥.

This poster clearly reads hero-led Western and that may be the role you booked because your type fits it.
But archetype-wise, that ‚Äúhero‚Äù could be ùóñùóÆùóøùó≤ùó¥ùó∂ùòÉùó≤ùóø / ùó•ùó≤ùóØùó≤ùóπ / ùó•ùòÇùóπùó≤ùóø / ùó†ùóÆùó¥ùó∂ùó∞ùó∂ùóÆùóª / ùóúùóªùóªùóºùó∞ùó≤ùóªùòÅ and that choice changes everything.

What an incredible evening it was to be interviewed by the wonderful Victoria Beale Live with a studio audience at the 'Business Growth Crowd - Global Podcast Networking with New London media in London bridge today!

The full interview is in the editing stage right now, but I wanted to share this snippet in the meantime!

# **CASTING CALL **

Hi,

I am Pragati Gupta, seeking actors for short scenes to be filmed for a graduate film directing class at UNCW.

Here is the breakdown for the ‚ÄúSorry We Missed You‚Äù scene recreation.

*Scene brief:* When a working-class father discovers his teenage son‚Äôs quiet rebellion, the family is forced to confront the cost of survival versus the promise of a better future.

**SEB**: 15-18 yrs old, (Male, Teenage son, Actors 18+ who can convincingly play younger are welcome.)

**ABBIE**: 40-50 yrs old, (Female, Mother, Calm authority, controlled intensity)

Actors will need to be available on **Wednesday, Feb 11, from 8:30am-12pm**. The shoot location will be on the UNCW Campus.

Submit the following (headshot, acting resume, video audition) to pg7528@uncw.edu.

Subject line: ‚ÄúCharacter Name‚Äù in ‚ÄúSorry We Missed You‚Äù.

Please include-

Name:

Age:

Recent photo:

Acting resume:

Submissions must be received by the morning of **Feb 4, 2026**.

items.text:
üé¨ **CAST & CREW CALL ‚Äì INDEPENDENT THRILLER FILM (1-DAY SHOOT)**
üìç Forney, Texas | One Location | Psychological Thriller

Hi everyone ‚Äî
I‚Äôm producing and directing a contained psychological thriller titled *Unraveled Vows*, and I‚Äôm looking to collaborate with passionate actors and crew members who want to be part of something cinematic, intimate, and festival-ready.

This is a low-budget, high-quality indie film designed to be shot in one day, one house, with only 3 main characters ‚Äî very performance-driven and story-focused.

The finished film will be pitched to executives, producers, and streaming platforms, and everyone involved will receive ownership/percentage participation in the project, not just a credit.

If you want to help build something meaningful instead of just another gig, this is for you.

üé≠ **CASTING (3 Principal Roles)**

**James (Male, 30‚Äì40)**
Charismatic, calm, rising politician. Loving husband with a darker, calculated side.

**Fatima (Female, late 20s‚Äìearly 30s)**
Emotionally layered, vulnerable but strong. Carries guilt and secrets. Lead role.

**Ken (Male, 30‚Äì40)**
Charming but dangerous. Quiet, psychological menace. Intense presence.

(Strong acting ability required ‚Äì dialogue-heavy roles)

üé• **CREW NEEDED**

‚Ä¢ Camera Operator / DP
‚Ä¢ Sound Recordist / Boom Mic Owner
‚Ä¢ Editor
‚Ä¢ Sound Design / Post Audio
‚Ä¢ PA (optional)

If you own gear (camera, boom, audio equipment), huge plus.

ü§ù **What You Get**

‚Ä¢ Ownership/percentage participation in the film
‚Ä¢ IMDb credit
‚Ä¢ Festival + streaming exposure
‚Ä¢ Transportation stipend
‚Ä¢ Food provided
‚Ä¢ 1-day shoot only
‚Ä¢ Collaborative, creative environment

This is perfect for actors and filmmakers building reels, credits, and real projects.

CASTING CALL ‚Äì JAPANESE HOSTS
Non-Union | Location: DTLA

Rehearsal: Sat 2/21

Shoot Dates: Sun 2/22 & Mon 2/23

Seeking vibrant, dynamic, camera-friendly Japanese-speaking hosts for an on-camera pop-up experience featuring the latest Japanese tech devices. Talent must be fluent in Japanese (bilingual preferred), energetic, welcoming, and comfortable interacting with real guests on camera. Strong improv skills and live-event energy are a plus.

ROLES:

‚Ä¢ Hiro ‚Äì Male, 20‚Äì40, Asian | Principal | $500/12

‚Ä¢ Sakura ‚Äì Female, 20‚Äì40, East Asian | Principal | $450/12

REQUIREMENTS:

Hosts will guide guests through a hands-on tech experience, demonstrating and showcasing new Japanese devices in a fun, engaging way. Must be confident speaking on camera, engaging the public, and adapting naturally in a live, filmed environment.

SUBMIT:

‚Ä¢ Headshot

‚Ä¢ Resume

‚Ä¢ Reel (if available)

‚Ä¢ Social media handles

‚Ä¢ 30‚Äì60 second audition video introducing yourself and welcoming guests to try the latest Japanese tech devices.

Please demonstrate how you would guide and excite guests, and mix in Japanese language naturally (greetings, explanations, reactions, or commentary).

Send submissions to:

üìß liferunner01@gmail.com

Include your name, email, and contact information.

#castingcalls #greatbritishbakeoffmusical #casting #castingcall

The Brookside Theatre are looking for the last few 'contestants' to join their amazing cast for their charity production of THE GREAT BRITISH BAKE OFF MUSICAL 

Roles:

GEMMA (Female identifying - playing age 30s) Mezzo Belt.

A carer from Blackpool

BEN (Male identifying - playing age 30s/40s) Baritone/Tenor 

A widowed police officer from Bristol; single dad to Lily 

HASSAN (Male identifying - playing age 17-25) Baritone/Tenor - Needs to rap
An A-Level Student from London (Middle Eastern Heritage)

RUSSELL (Male identifying - playing age 45-70) Baritone/Tenor - Flamboyant aeronautic engineer

DEZZA (Male identifying - playing age 25-50) Baritone/Tenor

A Vegan who lives on a houseboat

Production runs 6th - 10th May 2026

Venue: Brookside Theatre, Romford (2 mins walk from Lizzie Line / Free Parking)

Rehearsals: Monday & Wednesday evenings & Sunday daytimes by a schedule starting immediately at the theatre 

Profit Share production

If you are interested or know someone that might be right for any of these roles please get in touch either by PM or email casting@brooksidetheatre.com

These are the faces everyone will be talking about in 2026‚Ä¶ and this is where they learned their craft.

Some trained at Juilliard.  
Some at RADA, LAMDA, or The Lir.  
One went to Oxford School of Drama, another to a little conservatory in Cleveland.  
And one? Zero formal training at all.

There is no single ‚Äúright‚Äù way.  
There‚Äôs only your way ‚Äî and the training that helps you find it.

If you‚Äôre sitting there thinking ‚Äúthat could be me one day,‚Äù then start where they started: with the right school, the right teachers, and the right group of people who believe in you.

Your future co-stars are already training.  

Where are you?

#ActingSchool #FutureStars #ClassOf2026

items.text:
**CASTING CALL FOR WEB SERIES**

Hi everyone! I‚Äôm seeking actors for the first episode in a comedy web series, *Vancouver I Think We Should See Other Cities*. It revolves around a young man navigating the surreal everyday life of the Canadian city.

This first episode titled ‚ÄúTurn Down The Heat‚Äù is surreal but also risqu√© in what I hope is the best way possible. It‚Äôs important to note that nothing of graphic nature is ever depicted onscreen. 

My number one priority is ensuring a welcome and safe environment where we are able to collaborate on a strong project. If you have any questions regarding the material before submitting, please DM me and I am more than happy to discuss. 

**Logline:**

A young man, Paul, goes to a meeting of the Hudson Williams Fan Club only to realize that he may be out of his depth.

**Production Details:**
* Location: Vancouver, BC
* Filming Dates: Latter half of February 2026 (TBD)
* Non-Union / Volunteer
* Food and IMDb credit provided

**ROLES**

**STEVEN - Male, Mid-Late 20s (Open Ethnicity)**

The charismatic leader of the Hudson Williams Fan Club.

**JULIA - Female, Mid-Late 20s (Open Ethnicity)**

A member of the Hudson Williams Fan Club. She is understanding and supportive to Paul when he needs it.

**HUDSON WILLIAMS FAN CLUB MEMBERS - Mid-Late 20s (Open Ethnicity)**

The rest of the group, unfazed by the events of the meeting. 

**TO APPLY**

Please send the following to [vaithinkweshouldseeothercities@gmail.com](mailto:vaithinkweshouldseeothercities@gmail.com)

Subject: ‚ÄúEPISODE #1 - [CHARACTER NAME]‚Äù
* Headshot
* Resume
* Demo reel (if possible)
* Availability (Latter half of February 2026)

Thank you so much for your time. Take care and have a great day.

Has a dispute got out of hand?

Do you want to draw a line under a conflict that‚Äôs been going on too long?

In this brand-new series, from the makers of *Long Lost Family,* we‚Äôll open the doors of a fast-track court that will help people settle their civil disputes.

**CASTING CALL ‚Äì JENNY & POPPY (Newcastle)** 

We are currently casting **two key female roles** for a Newcastle-based short film / pilot being produced as part of a university project.

**Roles:**

**JENNY (mid - late 20s)**
Confident, sharp, and socially switched-on. Jenny is witty, emotionally intelligent, and often the voice of reason within the group. Strong presence on screen.

**POPPY (mid - late 20s)**

items.text:
Strike a Pose: A Fashion Fairytale
Film Auditions 

It is a non paid film

Overview: Elssya Morgan wants more than anything to be a fashion designer. But her aunt Heather and cousins won‚Äôt let that happen. But when millionaires, the Windors, throw a party for their son and invite all the top designers in Michigan to the party. Elyssa takes her chance to show her talent to everyone and maybe steal the heart of Jake Windsor. 

If you‚Äôre interested in auditioning, please send your headshot, resume, and reel to cecem143@gmail.com. Once you send your information over, you will receive sides to do a self-tape. We will accept them until February 15th, 2026, at 11:59 pm. (if you‚Äôre auditioning for Jake, and you get an email back after your self-tape, you will be asked to do a chemistry test with the lead actress.)Filming locations are Birmingham, Royal Oak, and the Metro Detroit Area. Looking forward to hearing from you all. 

Jake Windsor - African American, dark hair, mid 20s, charming, handsome, well-dressed, tall, smart, he has dreams for his future, and he hates being controlled by his parents.

Heather Morgan - White, in her mid-30s, Elyssa‚Äôs aunt, wicked, wears fancy clothes, mean, rude, selfish, tries to make herself look young for her age, has two daughters, Giselle and Clarissa.

Giselle Morgan - White, in her mid-20s, Elyssa's cousin, spoiled brat, mean, demanding, nasty, wears too much makeup, dresses fashionably, acts like she‚Äôs better than everyone else, 

Clarissa Morgan - White, in her mid 20s, Elyssa's cousin, mean, thinks of herself as a spoiled brat, rude, bossy, dresses fashionably, acts like she‚Äôs better than everyone else, wears too much makeup.

Ryan Chanel- White, in his mid 20s, flamboyant, positive, energetic, charismatic, witty, introspective, and fashionable, Elyssa's best friend.

Henry Levell- African American, in his mid 30s, posh, elegant, witty, mildly sarcastic, he is Jake‚Äôs family butler and always tries to have Jake‚Äôs back.

Ruby Windsor - African American, she‚Äôs in her mid 30s to early 40s, Jake‚Äôs mom,  snobby, elegant, sophisticated, pushy, noisy, sometimes funny, controlling, acts like a know-it-all, dresses well.

Christopher Windsor - African American, he‚Äôs in his mid 30s to early 40s, Jake‚Äôs dad, smart, sometimes stuck up, snobby, sometimes pushy, dresses well, businessman, wants his son to run the family business

topComments.text: Unless it's a student film ALWAYS pay your cast and crew!

## üåµ CASTING CALL: "DEAD OR ALIVE" (SAG Short Film / Western) üåµ

Seeking lead talent for an upcoming SAG-AFTRA short film shooting in **Agua Dulce, CA**. We are looking for two powerhouse actors to lead this gritty, character-driven Western.

**PAY:** $200/day + Copy, Credit, and Meals. 

**SHOOT DATES:** February 21st & 22nd, 2026. 
IMDB: [https://www.imdb.com/title/tt39387683](https://www.imdb.com/title/tt39387683)
Director: Nick Montalvo 
Producer: 

üìÜ UPDATED DEADLINES & AUDITIONS 
* **SUBMISSION DEADLINE:** Monday, Feb 9th, 2026 @ 10:00 PM.
* **IN-PERSON AUDITIONS:** Wednesday, Feb 11th, 2026.
* **LOCATION:** Los Angeles / The Valley (NoHo/Studio City area).
üé≠ ROLES

**[WESLEY] ‚Äì LEAD** Male, 30-45. A hardened lawman who's fallen onto desperate times. Steadfast and no-nonsense. He hides his emotions well but is determined to right the world‚Äôs wrongs at all costs. We meet him as a weary man.

**[FRANCIS] ‚Äì LEAD** Male, 25-35. A dangerous outlaw and Wesley's estranged younger brother. Unpredictable, brash, and uneasy. Behind the tough exterior is a hurt kid desperate to keep everyone out.

**STORYLINE:** A disgraced Sheriff seeks help from his estranged outlawed younger brother to save his ailing daughter, but intentions on both sides are not what they seem.

üì© 

**DO NOT DM headshots or reels.** To be considered, please email your materials to the address below. If you are a fit for the role, you will receive a reply with **SIDES** for the audition.

**EMAIL:** ClassicalCastings@gmail.com **SUBJECT:** [Role Name] - [Your Name] - Dead or Alive

Please include your headshot, resume, and a link to your reel/work samples.

Thanks in advance! 
Spencer, 
Producer

items.text:
Hi all!
I hope everyone is having a great week!

I'm Roisin, I'm 23 with a playing age of 16-26, based in Northamptonshire and I have bases in Bristol, Edinburgh and London. I am an actor, musician, and writer. 

I am looking to build my film showreel and connect with fellow creatives in and around the Midlands. I am interested in short films, indie projects and student films. 

Spotlight: 

https://www.spotlight.com/1019-4502-3895

Feel free to drop me a DM about any projects! 

Thanks!

Ro

items.text:
**CASTING SHOUT-OUT ‚Äî FEATURE ARTISTS (60+)**

We‚Äôre seeking two brilliant character actors (playing age 60+) to appear as a playful ‚ÄúRomeo & Juliet‚Äù duo in the spirit of Compo & Nora Batty (Last of the Summer Wine) for a one-day scene in our Yorkshire-based feature film. This cameo will with our main cast, a handful of lines each, and plenty of cheeky northern charm.

**Details**

Roles:** ‚ÄúRomeo‚Äù & ‚ÄúJuliet‚Äù (feature artists, a few lines each)
Vibe:** Warm, witty, gently combative banter, think mismatched soulmates with decades of history, twinkle in the eye and spark in the step
Equity** rates (Feature Artist)
Shoot Window:** **Third week of February** (one day)

**To apply (ASAP):**

* Email kathryn@bad-fox.com with subject: **‚ÄúROMEO/JULIET ‚Äî YOUR NAME ‚Äî 60+‚Äù**
* Include: Spotlight link or CV, headshot(s), short reel (comedy welcome), location/postcode, availability for the **third week of February**
* Please note if you are 1 hour of Bridlington**

* We welcome submissions from all backgrounds and encourage local talent.
* Finalists may be asked for a short self-tape 

This is a joyful, good-humoured day on set, come have a laugh and steal the scene! üé¨

sharedPost.text:
Liebe Produktionen, Produzenten aber auch liebe Agenturen und Filmschaffende in Deutschland:

+++ Der  erste Gagenkatalog f√ºr Kompars*innen und Kleindarsteller*innen ist seit ein paar Tagen √∂ffentlich! +++

Die darin angegebenen Betr√§ge sind Empfehlungen der Initiative Faire Gagen und beruhen auf den Erfahrungen vieler etablierter Filmschaffender und ihren R√ºckmeldungen an unsere Initiative, als auch auf Gespr√§che unsererseits mit Agenturen und Produktionen. 
 
Dabei werden auch schrittweise gew√§hlte Ziele des Katalogs (z.B. von budget-schw√§cheren Produktionen) zu mehr Fairness und damit auch wieder zu h√∂herer Motivation der Filmschaffenden f√ºhren.

Nachweislich kommt es gerade durch etablierte Filmschaffende zu weniger Problemen beim Buchungsprocedere und ganz besonders am Set, als bei st√§ndig neu gecasteten Menschen, die eben oft ganz andere Beweggr√ºnde haben, wie z.B. "einfach mal dabei sein" und dies auch selbst f√ºr eigentlich nicht mehr Faire Gagen. 

Dazu jedoch nur als Beispiel, die bekanntlich  immer h√∂her steigende Zahl von kurzfristigen Buchungs-Absagen und dabei besonders das Nichterscheinen am Drehort ohne Absage, festgebuchter Kompars*innen. 
Besonders letzteres sehen selbstverst√§ndlich auch wir als ein absolutes "No Go" gegen√ºber unseren Produktionen und Agenturen an.

+++ Eine faire Bezahlung aber auch das schrittweise Umdenken bez√ºglich veralteter Setregeln, oder kaum noch nachvollziebarer Buchungsbeschr√§nkungen (Beispiel Altersgrenzen) wird, verbunden mit  einer h√∂heren Wertsch√§tzung gegen√ºber den Filmschaffenden,  nicht nur zu  einem besseren Arbeitsklima f√ºhren, sondern zwangsl√§ufig auch ein Garant f√ºr direkte  Zeit- und Kosteneinsparungen der Produktionen sein. +++

Auch die Agenturen k√∂nnten so zumindest bei dem f√ºr jede Produktion so wichtigen Faktor "Zeit" profitieren und so noch effizienter und professioneller f√ºr ihre zu betreuenden Produktionen arbeiten.
Tats√§chlich werden nur so beide Seiten mittel- und langfristig provitieren. 
Der leider oft voreilig eingesetzte  Rotstift mancher Produktionen hat bereits viele etablierte und zuverl√§ssige Filmschaffende in den letzten  Jahren zwangsl√§ufig verprellt. 

Daher sehen wir auch ganz allgemein, dass eine Philosophie von "Einsparungen" und "Weiter so" (auf einem sich nicht mehr lohnenden Gagen-Niveau) dem deutschen Film eher schaden als n√ºtzen wird.
Produktionen, die sich eh schon an faire Gagen und Zuschl√§ge halten sind hier nat√ºrlich weniger angesprochen. Sie dienen f√ºr uns jedoch als absolut beispielhaft f√ºr alle anderen, denn sie zeigen uns schon seit vielen Jahren sehr eindrucksvoll, dass Fairness und Wertsch√§tzung eben doch ganz einfach funktioniert.

Initiative Faire Gagen.

items.text:
Hi everyone!

I‚Äôm starting to explore entertainment companies that are remote or mostly hybrid and would love any insight. This can be in film, TV, music, sports, or any creative space.

I‚Äôm based in San Diego and own a home here, so ideally I‚Äôm looking for something that allows flexibility to go back and forth to LA when needed, but not be fully office-based.

For background, I‚Äôm a business attorney, but I‚Äôm open to roles in legal or business affairs, as well as non-legal roles where a legal background is still a strong asset.

If you know of any companies that are remote or hybrid-friendly, even if they are not hiring right now, I would be so grateful to hear about them.

items.text:
Casting Call (Non-Union) for ALL AGES, ALL DEMOGRAPHICS - Paid

Looking for actors to play the role of a client in a simulated therapy or counselling session. The video clips will be used in an online training system for counselors and psychologists. For this round of sessions we are planning both longer form scripted and shorter improv shoots.

We are currently especially interested in meeting actors who identify as queer or trans, and we are also very interested in actors who identify as Asian or latinx.

However, all ages, all gender expressions/identities, all ethnicities, and persons with disabilities are absolutely welcome.

All experience levels with acting are welcome. We are committed to making this a respectful and safe process, with open communication and respect for boundaries.

Comfortable English fluency is required.

Immediate filming dates are February 3 to February 20, based on actor availability, but our needs are ongoing and more will occur in the future, so please submit if you're interested at all.

Location is downtown Vancouver - Gastown. Pay is $60 CAD per hour, with the expectation of some prepared material, studio session duration: 1-2 hours. If there is some significant preparation required, compensation is offered for that time.

Please email phil@skillsetter.com with your headshot and resume, as well as some information about you, such as gender identity, age, cultural/racial background. If you've submitted for a past session, you're welcome to submit again. We do sometimes receive more submissions than we are able to respond to, but we do read them all, and we do save your submissions for future consideration.

description.text:
Dear Artists and Cultural Shapers,

The Call for Artists for the 2026 Quilombo Experience Residency is now officially open.

Led by Creative Director Luana Dias David, this six-session paid incubator is designed for dancers, musicians, poets, and storytellers (ages 15+) to deepen their craft through Afro-Brazilian ancestral roots and cultural leadership.

Residency Highlights:

- Cultural Immersion: Workshops on Afro-Brazilian history and ancestral traditions led by Luana and guest artists.
- Creative Agency: A collaborative environment where artists blend their personal styles into a work-in-progress.
- Professional Assets: Participants receive professional photography and video of their work from the final showcase.
- Stipend: Selected artists will receive a $600 stipend.

The Commitment:

- Dates: March 15, March 29, April 12, April 26 and 
May 3rd.
- Format: 3-hour intensive creative lab followed by a 1-hour public community sharing.

How to Apply: 

Use QR code or WhatsApp number +1 4133298959 and fill the google Form. Applications are open from February 2nd through March 1st.

This opportunity is funded by the Equity Fund of the Berkshire Taconic Community Foundation.
We thank Jacob's Pillow for its constant support and sponsorship.

üé¨ DENVER / AURORA FILMMAKERS ‚Äî VOLUNTEER CREW CALL (IMDb CREDIT) üé¨
I‚Äôm filming a documentary in Lyons, CO on Monday, February 9, and I‚Äôm looking for a small volunteer crew‚Äîespecially a Director of Photography‚Äîto help capture an important story.

This film has been built entirely by volunteers‚Äîpeople who believe stories can actually change systems. We‚Äôre keeping the crew small, intentional, and respectful of everyone‚Äôs time.

### üé• Roles Needed:

‚Ä¢ Director of Photography (priority)  

‚Ä¢ Assistant Camera (AC)  

‚Ä¢ Lighting / Gaffer  

‚Ä¢ Production Assistant (PA)

### üìç Shoot Details:

üìÖ Monday, Feb 9  

üìç Anschutz Medical Campus ‚Äì Aurora, CO  

üéû Documentary (mental health, prevention, community)  

üé¨ IMDb credit provided  

‚è± Short, focused shoot day

This project centers on mental health prevention, belonging, and real human stories‚Äînot spectacle, not fluff. If you‚Äôre a DP or crew member who cares about purpose-driven filmmaking, meaningful collaboration, and telling stories that actually matter, I‚Äôd love to connect.

Please comment or DM with:

‚Ä¢ The role you‚Äôre interested in  

‚Ä¢ A link to your work, reel, or IG (if you have one)

Even sharing this with someone in your network helps more than you know.  

Thank you üíô

items.text:
Hello all, we are looking for actors for a CU Denver student film shooting this march 

Title: The Scare

Genre: Drama, Period 

Synopsis: Terry is a normal kid having a normal childhood, with two small exceptions: her father is an American spy living in West Berlin at the height of the Cold War, and she is gradually going deaf in both ears. Every day she goes to school, does her homework, plays with dolls, and every night her family plays a game of "Scare," which unbeknownst to her, is preparation for an impending Russian invasion

Roles - 

Terry Galloway (10-12): A young girl trying to live a normal life in Berlin during the Cold War. She's also going deaf in both ears. Terry is feisty but afraid of the immense changes undertaking her life.

Trudy Galloway (14-15): Terry's older sister, anxious and too aware for her own good. 

Tenley Galloway (7-8): Terry's little sister, naive and oblivious. 

Paul (30-40): Terry's father, and a spy for the American military during the Cold War. Kind, good natured, and a natural liar.

Edna (25-40): Terry's mother. Anxious about the fate of her children. 

Edith (25-40): The family's maid. (German accent required)

Note: additional smaller roles needed, not listed 

Director, Writer: Sophii Sherman 

Based on: Mean Little Deaf Queer, Written by Terry Galloway

Producers: Dominic Spacone, Christine Galvez

Production Type: Student Film

Contact Information: Sophiisherman@gmail.com

Run Time: Short (~10 mins)

Compensation: Unpaid

Union Status: Non-Union

Audition Information: Auditions are all online and will be reviewed and casted this February 

Shooting Schedule: ~mar 12-22 - 4 day shooting schedule will fall sometime within that time span depending on actor availability

Filming Location: Denver

If you are interested scan the QR code or email and reach out!

Synopsis: Terry is a normal kid having a normal childhood, with two small exceptions: her father is an American spy living in West Berlin at the height of the Cold War, and she is gradually going deaf in both ears. Every day she goes to school, does her homework, plays with dolls, and every night her family plays a game of "Scare," which unbeknownst to her, is preparation for an impending Russian invasion

Roles - 

Terry Galloway (10-12): A young girl trying to live a normal life in Berlin during the Cold War. She's also going deaf in both ears. Terry is feisty but afraid of the immense changes undertaking her life.

Trudy Galloway (14-15): Terry's older sister, anxious and too aware for her own good. 

Tenley Galloway (7-8): Terry's little sister, naive and oblivious. 

Paul (30-40): Terry's father, and a spy for the American military during the Cold War. Kind, good natured, and a natural liar.

Edna (25-40): Terry's mother. Anxious about the fate of her children. 

Edith (25-40): The family's maid. (German accent required)

Note: additional smaller roles needed, not listed 

Director, Writer: Sophii Sherman 

Based on: Mean Little Deaf Queer, Written by Terry Galloway

Producers: Dominic Spacone, Christine Galvez

Production Type: Student Film

Contact Information: Sophiisherman@gmail.com

Run Time: Short (~10 mins)

Compensation: Unpaid

Union Status: Non-Union

Audition Information: Auditions are all online and will be reviewed and casted this February 

Shooting Schedule: ~mar 12-22 - 4 day shooting schedule will fall sometime within that time span depending on actor availability

Filming Location: Denver

If you are interested scan the QR code or email and reach out!

Title: Saturdays

Genre: Thriller/Comedy

Logline: After accidentally taking a new designer drug on the way to a Halloween party, three broke nobodies become viral vigilantes in a city on the edge but their rise to infamy puts them in the cross-hairs of a charismatic cartel leader.

Role:

Dave (30-50) Unkillable, unshakable, and possibly unmedicated. Somehow still endearing. Dave is an uber driver, a hype man, and a secret weapon and comes from a different era. He‚Äôs the uncle at thanksgiving that you hope didn‚Äôt bring a bottle of scotch (you know he did). A chaotic wildcard who might be a genius... or just very, very lucky.

Production Type: Indie

Production Company: Loste Films

Contact Information: [luke@lostefilms.com](mailto:luke@lostefilms.com)

Run Time: Feature

Compensation: Catering/Crafty provided during proof of concept shoot. Compensation for future shoot dates is open to negotiation.

Audition Information: Send an email with headshot, resume and reel. The first round of auditions will be self-tape, then we will have in-person callbacks (downtown Denver area).

Shooting Schedule: Late February. Other shoot dates TBD

Filming Location: Highlands Ranch and Denver area

Project Description: Saturdays is an upcoming feature film we‚Äôre currently shooting the beginning of to use as a proof of concept. The scenes in the proof of concept are still being used in the final movie, which will be shot later on in the year. Due to scheduling conflicts we had to recast this role and are looking for someone who can carry mystery, comedy, and spiritual invincibility. There‚Äôs also lots of room for improv in the role. Some character inspirations include Erlich Eachman (Silicon Valley), Frank Reynolds (It‚Äôs Always Sunny), Red (Pineapple Express), Jay (Clerks), The Dude (The Big Lebowski). Attached pictures are the location/vehicles we have locked in for the first scene you‚Äôll be shooting with us.

**Logline:**
Als eine junge Frau beginnt, ihre Beziehung mit einem anderen Paar zu vergleichen, verliert sie den Blick f√ºr die Liebe, die direkt vor ihr steht.

**Gesuchte Rollen (alle ca. 19‚Äì25 Jahre):**

**Weibliche Hauptrolle**
Junge Frau in ihrer ersten ernsthaften Beziehung. Unsicher, emotional offen, stark von √§u√üeren Erwartungen und Vergleichen beeinflusst. Die Rolle erfordert ein sensibles Spiel innerer Konflikte und leiser emotionaler Ver√§nderungen.

**M√§nnliche Hauptrolle**
Ihr Freund. Bodenst√§ndig, ruhig und bem√ºht. Er liebt ehrlich, ger√§t aber zunehmend unter Druck, weil er den Erwartungen seiner Partnerin nicht gerecht werden kann. Subtiles, zur√ºckgenommenes Spiel ist wichtig.

**Weibliche Nebenrolle**
Junge Frau mit perfekter Au√üenwirkung. Kontrolliert und diszipliniert, privat jedoch angespannt. Die Rolle lebt vom Kontrast zwischen √§u√üerer Kontrolle und innerer Unsicherheit.

items.text:
PAID OPPORTUNITY
We are casting an actress (35-45 playing age) for the role of Janice in our 10-minute student short film Elvis Died for This.

Set in 1985, the Wright family are barely holding it together. When the youngest son, Mikey, accidentally blows up their neighbour's beloved guinea pig, Elvis, in a homemade science experiment, the family scrambles to cover it up. As the chaos unravels, Mikey finally tells the truth - about the guinea pig, and about how broken his family really is. His honesty forces everyone to face reality, and the Wrights finally stop pretending to be a happy family.

No prior acting experience is required, so if this is something you are interested in, please do not hesitate to apply.

Shooting dates:

7/03/2026

14/03/2026

21/03/2026

22/03/2026

Applicants must be based in or near Falmouth, or close enough to travel to and from Falmouth each shooting weekend.

To apply or for more information email - eb300109@falmouth.ac.uk
